This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) tasks, specifically video colorization. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning (MM) techniques, such as neural networks, for training the colorization and refinement networks. Thus, cs.MM is the second most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of self-regularization and diversity in the loss functions, which are common topics in machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) research. Finally, the paper involves spatiotemporal constraints, which are relevant to graphics (GR) research.
